# Build Safety Rules (Cloudflare Pages / Next.js)

When editing pages or components, avoid these patterns that cause build failures:

## 1. Mismatched export default
- Ensure `export default X` matches the component name defined in the file (e.g. `const X: React.FC = () => ...`).
- Run `npm run find-mismatched-exports` before pushing to catch copy-paste errors.

## 2. Root-level template/backup files
- Files at project root (e.g. `OLD_LearnHub_BACKUP_Oct31_2025.tsx`, `EXAMPLE_CALCULATOR_IMPLEMENTATION.tsx`) use `../components/` imports that don't resolve from root.
- These are excluded in tsconfig.json/tsconfig.next.json. Do NOT remove them from exclude.

## 3. Not-found page
- The custom `app/not-found.tsx` must stay minimal (no Layout/Header/Sidebar).
- Main app routes live under `app/(main)/` so they get ClientLayoutWrapper. The not-found page does NOT use the heavy layout—this avoids "Failed to collect page data for /_not-found" during build.

## 4. Pages Router files (src/pages/)
- Every page file must have a default export. Empty or placeholder pages need `export default function X() { return <Navigate to="..." />; }` or similar.
